1
00:00:00,767 --> 00:00:05,567
(Episode 6: The Double Life of an Idol)

2
00:00:05,933 --> 00:00:09,300
(Trying to put him to sleep
for 20 minutes)

3
00:00:09,633 --> 00:00:11,367
(Still wide awake)

4
00:00:12,167 --> 00:00:13,167
Gosh.

5
00:00:13,167 --> 00:00:16,367
(His arms, back, knees,
and legs are starting to go numb.)

6
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:20,133
(He eventually flops down on the couch.)

7
00:00:20,433 --> 00:00:23,733
(Meanwhile, what is SOOBIN up to?)

8
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:26,433
(He unpacks the diaper bag
after a day out.)

9
00:00:26,733 --> 00:00:28,300
(First on the list, Yu Jun's raincoat)

10
00:00:28,733 --> 00:00:30,833
(Second, Yu Jun's utensils
and water bottle)

11
00:00:31,767 --> 00:00:33,567
(Third, Yu Jun's leftover snacks)

12
00:00:33,567 --> 00:00:35,800
(After putting them back,)

13
00:00:36,467 --> 00:00:40,767
(shall I finally take a break?)

14
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:43,433
Yu Jun.

15
00:00:43,433 --> 00:00:45,567
(A cry disturbs his rest.)

16
00:00:45,567 --> 00:00:46,767
(Chuckling)

17
00:00:47,267 --> 00:00:49,133
(Crying)

18
00:00:49,133 --> 00:00:51,067
(Wailing)

19
00:00:51,633 --> 00:00:55,000
(His break from parenting is over.)

20
00:00:56,333 --> 00:00:59,433
(Yu Jun has no intention of sleeping.)

21
00:00:59,433 --> 00:01:00,433
(Holding back laughter)

22
00:01:00,433 --> 00:01:02,000
Why isn't Yu Jun sleeping?

23
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:04,400
Hold him like this,

24
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:07,067
and make his head rest on your shoulder.

25
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:09,267
You're patting him too gently.

26
00:01:09,567 --> 00:01:10,633
Pat him harder.

27
00:01:10,633 --> 00:01:14,833
He'll fall asleep
if you walk around with him.

28
00:01:14,833 --> 00:01:16,133
It's tough, right?

29
00:01:16,133 --> 00:01:17,200
It's not easy.

30
00:01:17,700 --> 00:01:18,967
(Heave-ho)

31
00:01:19,467 --> 00:01:21,100
Rest his head on your shoulder.

32
00:01:21,100 --> 00:01:22,167
Aren't you sleepy?

33
00:01:23,367 --> 00:01:24,600
Why are you crying again?

34
00:01:24,633 --> 00:01:25,800
(Whining)

35
00:01:26,633 --> 00:01:29,000
(Yu Jun still fusses
despite YEONJUN's efforts.)

36
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,567
- This is driving me crazy.
- Why are you crying?

37
00:01:31,067 --> 00:01:33,000
(Fussing)

38
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:35,233
What's making you so upset?

39
00:01:37,267 --> 00:01:41,400
(A horn grows on Yu Jun's head.)

40
00:01:44,167 --> 00:01:45,900
(Sleepy)

41
00:01:45,900 --> 00:01:46,933
Oh, no. You're so upset.

42
00:01:46,933 --> 00:01:48,700
(A sleepy and upset 15-month-old)

43
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:51,000
Do you want to switch?
Or will you keep holding him?

44
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:53,233
If he cries again, let's switch.

45
00:01:53,233 --> 00:01:55,333
Okay. Sweet dreams, Yu Jun.

46
00:01:55,333 --> 00:01:56,967
(SOOBIN leaves again...)

47
00:01:57,667 --> 00:02:01,200
(and takes another break from parenting.)

48
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:06,433
(YEONJUN tries to get him
to sleep multiple times.)

49
00:02:06,933 --> 00:02:09,067
(Walking back...)

50
00:02:10,167 --> 00:02:12,367
(and forth)

51
00:02:14,067 --> 00:02:17,867
(But Yu Jun refuses to sleep.)

52
00:02:21,367 --> 00:02:22,633
What's wrong?

53
00:02:23,100 --> 00:02:25,900
(I don't know either!)

54
00:02:27,467 --> 00:02:29,067
(Surprised)

55
00:02:29,667 --> 00:02:32,267
(Yu Jun just won't fall asleep.)

56
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:34,700
(Giving up his break)

57
00:02:34,700 --> 00:02:36,333
Why won't he stop crying?

58
00:02:36,333 --> 00:02:38,100
(SOOBIN the Bed to the rescue)

59
00:02:38,100 --> 00:02:40,067
What am I doing wrong?
I think I'm doing fine.

60
00:02:40,067 --> 00:02:41,067
Why is he crying?

61
00:02:41,067 --> 00:02:42,800
Yu Jun usually doesn't cry much.

62
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:44,033
(No!)

63
00:02:44,033 --> 00:02:45,733
You'll soon get used to it, Yu Jun.

64
00:02:46,867 --> 00:02:48,467
He worked so hard. Let's let him go.

65
00:02:48,467 --> 00:02:49,500
(Don't go!)

66
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:52,533
He'll be right back.

67
00:02:53,033 --> 00:02:54,200
(You wanted to hold me earlier!)

68
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:55,767
He'll be back soon, Yu Jun.

69
00:02:55,833 --> 00:02:57,233
(Crying)

70
00:02:57,467 --> 00:02:58,600
Are you upset, Yu Jun?

71
00:02:58,600 --> 00:03:00,033
(You liked it before,
and now you're leaving!)

72
00:03:00,033 --> 00:03:01,367
It's okay.

73
00:03:02,033 --> 00:03:03,367
(I'm sorry, I love you.)

74
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:05,133
(Plopping down)

75
00:03:05,133 --> 00:03:06,267
What is it?

76
00:03:06,267 --> 00:03:08,500
(Even a one-sided love takes stamina.)

77
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:09,567
Are you feeling sick?

78
00:03:10,633 --> 00:03:13,133
You couldn't sleep much on our way here.

79
00:03:13,667 --> 00:03:15,367
You should sleep some more, right?

80
00:03:15,933 --> 00:03:16,967
Are you feeling better?

81
00:03:17,233 --> 00:03:18,233
Yes.

82
00:03:20,667 --> 00:03:22,967
(No wonder he's a nap-time expert.)

83
00:03:22,967 --> 00:03:24,067
You're okay now.

84
00:03:28,367 --> 00:03:34,433
(Yu Jun immediately rests his head
when his favorite bed pats him.)

85
00:03:35,300 --> 00:03:39,800
(SOOBIN casually sits on the edge.)

86
00:03:41,133 --> 00:03:45,900
(His feet show the reality of parenting.)

87
00:03:47,267 --> 00:03:51,167
(SOOBIN's nap routine for Yu Jun)

88
00:03:51,933 --> 00:03:52,933
(Patting)

89
00:03:52,933 --> 00:03:56,100
(Endlessly patting)

90
00:03:56,100 --> 00:04:00,900
(Busy knees
from nonstop walking and sitting)

91
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:01,900
(Patting)

92
00:04:01,900 --> 00:04:04,633
(Patting ASMR)

93
00:04:04,633 --> 00:04:06,000
(Yu Jun's head slowly droops.)

94
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:09,433
(Dropping)

95
00:04:09,433 --> 00:04:12,733
(Did he fall asleep?)

96
00:04:12,733 --> 00:04:14,600
(Sneaking in)

97
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:17,067
(YEONJUN goes back
to his favorite baby after recharging.)

98
00:04:17,067 --> 00:04:19,067
(Is he asleep?)

99
00:04:20,767 --> 00:04:21,900
(He notices YEONJUN.)

100
00:04:21,900 --> 00:04:23,933
(Did he fall asleep?)

101
00:04:25,167 --> 00:04:27,267
(He did.)

102
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:34,000
(Putting him down is the real challenge.)

103
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,000
(Careful)

104
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:39,400
(Patting)

105
00:04:39,833 --> 00:04:41,033
(Twitching)

106
00:04:41,033 --> 00:04:42,900
(They couldn't put him down.)

107
00:04:44,433 --> 00:04:45,533
SOOBIN.

108
00:04:45,533 --> 00:04:47,067
(Just do it fast.)

109
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:48,833
(Just do it quickly.)

110
00:04:49,967 --> 00:04:52,167
He'll wake up on the way down.

111
00:04:52,167 --> 00:04:53,200
(I see.)

112
00:04:54,100 --> 00:04:55,133
There.

113
00:04:55,667 --> 00:04:56,667
That's it.

114
00:04:57,133 --> 00:05:01,233
(Did he make it?)

115
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:02,500
(Whimpering)

116
00:05:03,333 --> 00:05:05,600
(He failed.)

117
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:07,167
How do I put him down?

118
00:05:07,167 --> 00:05:08,967
(How about this?)

119
00:05:08,967 --> 00:05:11,033
(Hold him...)

120
00:05:11,033 --> 00:05:12,467
(and roll over.)

121
00:05:12,467 --> 00:05:14,133
(Ta-da)

122
00:05:18,933 --> 00:05:24,667
(Should I at least try?)

123
00:05:24,667 --> 00:05:29,033
(SOOBIN the Bed goes
with YEONJUN the Bed's idea.)

124
00:05:29,267 --> 00:05:34,667
(Preparing to roll over)

125
00:05:37,067 --> 00:05:38,067
(Thumbs up)

126
00:05:38,067 --> 00:05:39,667
(Continuing to coach him)

127
00:05:39,667 --> 00:05:42,300
(Standing up)

128
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:45,267
(Roll over now!)

129
00:05:45,267 --> 00:05:46,267
(Whimpering)

130
00:05:46,267 --> 00:05:49,100
Hey, surprise!

131
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:51,067
It's an event for you, Yu Jun.

132
00:05:52,300 --> 00:05:54,900
(Putting Yu Jun down
while he's sleeping is the hardest.)

133
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:56,300
How do we put him down?

134
00:05:56,433 --> 00:05:57,567
I just don't get it.

135
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:00,633
(Focused on looking it up)

136
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:07,567
(First, lie backward while holding him.)

137
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:13,067
(Let's put him down later.)

138
00:06:13,067 --> 00:06:14,067
(Sneaking closer)

139
00:06:14,067 --> 00:06:18,333
(But YEONJUN doesn't give up.)

140
00:06:19,067 --> 00:06:21,433
(Can't you put him down?)

141
00:06:27,033 --> 00:06:29,233
(The video he searched earlier)

142
00:06:30,133 --> 00:06:33,000
(SOOBIN tries to focus on it.)

143
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,533
(Mission complete)

144
00:06:34,533 --> 00:06:36,000
(His proud back says it all.)

145
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:44,267
(Yawning in relief
after being of some help)

146
00:06:44,533 --> 00:06:45,533
(Sniffing)
(Breathing out)

147
00:06:46,533 --> 00:06:51,400
(Yu Jun falls fast asleep
on SOOBIN the Bed.)

148
00:06:54,700 --> 00:06:57,733
(Shifting)

149
00:06:57,733 --> 00:07:00,833
(SOOBIN shifts around
as if he's uncomfortable.)

150
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:04,833
(He struggles to fall asleep.)

151
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,000
(Breathing)

152
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,267
(Yu Jun's deep breathing startles
him awake.)

153
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,000
(What was that?)

154
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,467
(Processing)

155
00:07:14,667 --> 00:07:18,100
(Uncomfortable)

156
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:21,267
(Wiggling)

157
00:07:22,367 --> 00:07:26,667
(There's nowhere to put his long legs.)

158
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:31,300
(As a result, he gets
to watch Yu Jun sleep up close.)

159
00:07:31,300 --> 00:07:32,333
(Breathing out)

160
00:07:33,433 --> 00:07:34,433
(Exhaling)

161
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:36,800
(Breathing out)

162
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:41,333
(Stroking)

163
00:07:42,433 --> 00:07:46,033
(And so, the Choi trio falls asleep.)

164
00:07:46,033 --> 00:07:49,367
(Daddy Choi)

165
00:07:49,367 --> 00:07:53,133
(Mommy Choi and Baby Choi)

166
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:58,667
(4:10 p.m., after an hour-long nap)

167
00:07:59,133 --> 00:08:00,800
(SOOBIN gets up
after hearing Yu Jun wake up.)

168
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:01,900
Did you sleep well?

169
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,600
Wait, my mic.

170
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:05,667
Gosh.

171
00:08:05,667 --> 00:08:07,800
(Also fixing the mic that bothered him
while he slept)

172
00:08:08,833 --> 00:08:09,967
(Sniffing)

173
00:08:12,633 --> 00:08:13,967
Oh, dear.

174
00:08:13,967 --> 00:08:16,300
(Getting up right away
the moment he cries louder)

175
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:18,167
(Mic)

176
00:08:19,133 --> 00:08:23,600
(Look at SOOBIN holding Yu Jun
and fixing his mic with one hand.)

177
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:26,867
YEONJUN.

178
00:08:27,933 --> 00:08:29,933
We should go out
and give Yu Jun some snacks.

179
00:08:30,033 --> 00:08:31,600
Do we feed him now?

180
00:08:32,033 --> 00:08:33,067
Yes.

181
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,300
Let's go.

182
00:08:35,300 --> 00:08:36,333
Okay.

183
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:39,833
(Don't just respond. Get up, Dad.)

184
00:08:40,147 --> 00:08:41,380
Did you sleep well, Yu Jun?

185
00:08:43,133 --> 00:08:45,967
(Mom got some sleep, but is still tired.)

186
00:08:45,967 --> 00:08:48,167
(An obviously well-rested baby)

187
00:08:48,700 --> 00:08:50,767
(Their half-awake faces look alike.)

188
00:08:51,433 --> 00:08:54,600
(Dad finally gets up.)

189
00:08:56,267 --> 00:08:58,267
(You're up?)

190
00:08:58,267 --> 00:09:00,167
- Should we give him some fruit?
- Yes.

191
00:09:00,967 --> 00:09:04,333
(YEONJUN prepares fruit for Yu Jun
right after waking up.)

192
00:09:04,833 --> 00:09:08,400
(Struggling to peel an orange)

193
00:09:09,233 --> 00:09:12,900
(Meanwhile, the living room feels
warm and sweet.)

194
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:16,867
(He somehow gets it done.)

195
00:09:16,867 --> 00:09:18,633
(Where's the plate?)

196
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:21,967
(Whatever. I'll just go.)

197
00:09:23,667 --> 00:09:24,967
Snack time.

198
00:09:24,967 --> 00:09:27,133
Uncle YEONJUN brought something good.

199
00:09:27,700 --> 00:09:29,533
(Putting it on a cheese wrapper)

200
00:09:30,167 --> 00:09:31,567
(Starting off with cheese)

201
00:09:31,567 --> 00:09:33,067
- Do you want some cheese?
- Open up.

202
00:09:33,067 --> 00:09:34,067
(Opening up)

203
00:09:34,067 --> 00:09:35,133
(Taking a bite)

204
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:37,533
(More!)

205
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,133
What a good eater.

206
00:09:39,133 --> 00:09:40,633
- Tasty, right?
- Open up.

207
00:09:40,633 --> 00:09:42,667
(YEONJUN trying to feed him
vs. Yu Jun trying to eat on his own)

208
00:09:45,733 --> 00:09:47,667
He likes feeding himself.

209
00:09:47,667 --> 00:09:50,233
(A fan of his own handiwork)

210
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:53,533
(Yu Jun's cheese-eating show)

211
00:09:54,433 --> 00:09:55,767
Delicious, isn't it?

212
00:09:57,033 --> 00:09:58,100
He eats so well.

213
00:10:01,699 --> 00:10:03,432
He's a great eater.

214
00:10:05,138 --> 00:10:06,505
(Peeking)

215
00:10:06,505 --> 00:10:08,272
You keep wiping your hand here.

216
00:10:09,438 --> 00:10:10,705
(This time, it's an orange.)

217
00:10:10,705 --> 00:10:12,238
Orange.

218
00:10:13,338 --> 00:10:16,205
(It's their first time feeding him
an orange.)

219
00:10:17,238 --> 00:10:20,272
- He's taking every bite willingly.
- I think it's his first time trying this.

220
00:10:20,272 --> 00:10:21,305
Maybe it is.

221
00:10:21,938 --> 00:10:22,972
Is it good?

222
00:10:22,972 --> 00:10:24,238
I can tell he finds it sour.

223
00:10:24,838 --> 00:10:25,672
Is it sour?

224
00:10:25,672 --> 00:10:26,738
Can I try a piece?

225
00:10:26,738 --> 00:10:27,605
Sure.

226
00:10:27,605 --> 00:10:29,072
I want to try it too...

227
00:10:29,772 --> 00:10:31,072
It's probably sour.

228
00:10:32,672 --> 00:10:33,472
He's reaching for it.

229
00:10:33,472 --> 00:10:35,105
Can you give him half a slice?

230
00:10:35,105 --> 00:10:36,105
He still has some in his mouth.

231
00:10:36,105 --> 00:10:37,638
(Look at Yu Jun
in the corner of the frame.)

232
00:10:42,438 --> 00:10:43,805
Is it because I just brushed my teeth?

233
00:10:45,005 --> 00:10:46,105
It's so good.

234
00:10:46,105 --> 00:10:47,038
- Is it good?
- Yes.

235
00:10:47,572 --> 00:10:48,705
Sorry, Yu Jun.

236
00:10:49,105 --> 00:10:50,372
(Taking his snack right before his eyes.)

237
00:10:50,372 --> 00:10:52,172
YEONJUN is taking your snack.

238
00:10:53,072 --> 00:10:54,238
Open your mouth.

239
00:10:55,038 --> 00:10:57,338
(Did you see the orange slice
just disappear into my mouth?)

240
00:10:57,338 --> 00:10:58,396
You're eating well.

241
00:10:59,372 --> 00:11:02,105
(Regardless of what YEONJUN is doing,
he just keeps eating the orange.)

242
00:11:02,105 --> 00:11:02,872
I think he likes it.

243
00:11:02,872 --> 00:11:04,038
- Is it sweet?
- It is.

244
00:11:04,038 --> 00:11:05,305
- Really?
- It really is.

245
00:11:05,305 --> 00:11:07,238
I'll bring some strawberries.

246
00:11:07,872 --> 00:11:11,205
(Pulling the stems off the strawberries
with a fork)

247
00:11:13,672 --> 00:11:14,772
Want to try one?

248
00:11:15,072 --> 00:11:16,305
Strawberry.

249
00:11:16,305 --> 00:11:17,372
(The third round with strawberries)

250
00:11:20,505 --> 00:11:22,572
(These strawberries are really good.)

251
00:11:23,005 --> 00:11:24,038
You're such a good eater.

252
00:11:26,538 --> 00:11:30,238
(Munching the strawberries)

253
00:11:30,538 --> 00:11:31,538
This is a strawberry.

254
00:11:34,105 --> 00:11:35,672
You really like it, don't you?

255
00:11:36,772 --> 00:11:37,738
Gosh.

256
00:11:38,005 --> 00:11:39,105
I'll have it.

257
00:11:41,338 --> 00:11:43,672
(This time, he's taking it
without dropping it.)

258
00:11:43,672 --> 00:11:45,072
You're eating so well.

259
00:11:46,505 --> 00:11:48,705
He keeps reaching for more,
even with some still in his mouth.

260
00:11:50,472 --> 00:11:52,305
- Slow down.
- Slow down, Yu Jun.

261
00:11:52,305 --> 00:11:55,038
- Did your appetite suddenly explode?
- I know.

262
00:11:55,272 --> 00:11:57,438
(Well...)

263
00:11:57,438 --> 00:11:58,472
(Wiping without looking)

264
00:11:58,472 --> 00:11:59,538
Hey, watch where you're wiping.

265
00:11:59,938 --> 00:12:01,138
I'll go grab some tissues.

266
00:12:01,138 --> 00:12:02,338
Why did your appetite suddenly explode?

267
00:12:04,638 --> 00:12:07,238
(Where are my strawberries?)

268
00:12:07,505 --> 00:12:09,772
(Let's go find my strawberries!)

269
00:12:11,672 --> 00:12:12,705
Honk-honk.

270
00:12:13,638 --> 00:12:15,472
Yu Jun is shopping right now.

271
00:12:16,072 --> 00:12:18,205
- Here you are.
- You're eating well.

272
00:12:18,805 --> 00:12:21,305
Vroom! Let's go!

273
00:12:21,905 --> 00:12:23,238
Here is your strawberry, Yu Jun.

274
00:12:24,672 --> 00:12:25,738
(A big bite)

275
00:12:27,338 --> 00:12:29,138
(Keeping strawberries ready for Yu Jun)

276
00:12:29,702 --> 00:12:30,905
(When sitting, they're Yu Jun's height.)

277
00:12:30,905 --> 00:12:32,238
- Goodness.
- Good boy.

278
00:12:32,238 --> 00:12:34,438
Yu Jun, are you all recharged?

279
00:12:35,172 --> 00:12:37,605
(After finishing the last strawberry,)

280
00:12:38,205 --> 00:12:41,405
(Yu Jun's mood is now fully recharged.)

281
00:12:41,405 --> 00:12:42,338
You're excited, aren't you?

282
00:12:44,405 --> 00:12:46,838
(Why is he suddenly getting fussy?)

283
00:12:46,838 --> 00:12:47,772
Did he poop?

284
00:12:48,501 --> 00:12:52,001
(We'll check your diaper for a second.)

285
00:12:52,072 --> 00:12:53,805
Time for an inspection, Yu Jun.

286
00:12:53,805 --> 00:12:55,972
Don't worry, be happy

287
00:12:55,972 --> 00:12:57,582
Oh, he peed.

288
00:12:58,005 --> 00:12:59,872
Oh, my goodness!

289
00:13:01,138 --> 00:13:03,538
All right. Sorry, we noticed so late.

290
00:13:03,538 --> 00:13:04,938
(What took you so long?)

291
00:13:05,372 --> 00:13:07,038
It's done!

292
00:13:07,038 --> 00:13:08,138
Diaper change complete!

293
00:13:09,572 --> 00:13:10,972
- We put his diaper on backward.
- No,

294
00:13:10,972 --> 00:13:12,605
we've been putting it on this way
the whole time.

295
00:13:12,805 --> 00:13:14,605
(The staff is telling them
the diaper is backward.)

296
00:13:14,605 --> 00:13:15,838
We've put it on backward all this time.

297
00:13:15,838 --> 00:13:16,705
No way.

298
00:13:17,738 --> 00:13:19,338
(After changing his diaper
before heading out)

299
00:13:19,338 --> 00:13:20,338
Okay.

300
00:13:20,638 --> 00:13:22,272
Wait. I think it's backward.

301
00:13:22,272 --> 00:13:24,438
- The front is in the back?
- I think they are.

302
00:13:24,438 --> 00:13:25,705
This side is sticking out too much.

303
00:13:25,705 --> 00:13:28,938
(An overwhelming sense of deja vu)

304
00:13:29,872 --> 00:13:33,538
(Thinking they put it on backward,
they change it again.)

305
00:13:34,838 --> 00:13:37,738
(This side is supposed to go on the back.)

306
00:13:38,638 --> 00:13:41,272
(They had it on correctly,
but ended up putting it on the wrong way.)

307
00:13:41,905 --> 00:13:45,538
I'm not sure if he peed or if it's
just wet, but we should change him later.

308
00:13:47,105 --> 00:13:48,138
(The tabs should be on the back.)

309
00:13:48,138 --> 00:13:50,072
That's why it leaked earlier.

310
00:13:50,872 --> 00:13:51,938
Sorry. Okay.

311
00:13:51,938 --> 00:13:53,038
(Crying)

312
00:13:53,038 --> 00:13:54,038
All right.

313
00:13:54,038 --> 00:13:55,938
(You guys should try wearing
your underwear backward too.)

314
00:13:55,938 --> 00:13:56,772
No.

315
00:13:56,772 --> 00:13:59,438
(YEONJUN is trying to comfort
upset Yu Jun.)

316
00:14:05,905 --> 00:14:08,972
(Confused by YEONJUN mimicking)

317
00:14:09,905 --> 00:14:11,805
Yu Jun, the louder person wins.

318
00:14:12,405 --> 00:14:14,472
(Dads often do weird things
instead of comforting their crying baby.)

319
00:14:14,472 --> 00:14:16,105
Yu Jun, you lost.

320
00:14:18,105 --> 00:14:19,138
Did I startle you?

321
00:14:19,838 --> 00:14:21,072
(I got startled.)

322
00:14:23,238 --> 00:14:25,238
(Seriously, what was that?)

323
00:14:28,038 --> 00:14:31,238
(YEONJUN's unexpected reaction
shuts down Yu Jun's crying mode.)

324
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:33,705
It works.

325
00:14:34,472 --> 00:14:36,505
(Feeling wronged somehow)

326
00:14:37,372 --> 00:14:38,972
(Yu Jun's crying button activates again.)

327
00:14:43,805 --> 00:14:45,738
(What is this feeling?)

328
00:14:46,072 --> 00:14:48,172
(The back of his head looks
full of thoughts.)

329
00:14:48,172 --> 00:14:51,172
(Watching)

330
00:14:52,238 --> 00:14:54,438
(Should I cry or not?)

331
00:14:54,772 --> 00:14:57,205
(I'm confused now.)

332
00:14:57,205 --> 00:14:58,938
Yu Jun, should we put your pants on now?

333
00:14:58,938 --> 00:15:00,405
(Has he finally calmed down?)

334
00:15:00,405 --> 00:15:01,338
No?

335
00:15:07,772 --> 00:15:10,205
(Stop copying me.)

336
00:15:12,205 --> 00:15:14,105
(I want to cry.)

337
00:15:16,338 --> 00:15:19,605
(He'll make that weird noise again
if I start wailing, won't he?)

338
00:15:19,605 --> 00:15:21,372
Please wipe his runny nose with this.

339
00:15:21,372 --> 00:15:22,205
Right.

340
00:15:22,205 --> 00:15:24,105
(Time to change his bib)

341
00:15:26,405 --> 00:15:28,138
(Crying mode off)

342
00:15:28,138 --> 00:15:29,872
(Crying mode on)

343
00:15:32,172 --> 00:15:33,805
What?

344
00:15:33,805 --> 00:15:35,905
What is it this time?

345
00:15:35,905 --> 00:15:37,205
It's all right.

346
00:15:37,738 --> 00:15:38,572
Let's look outside.

347
00:15:40,005 --> 00:15:43,705
(In the end,
Mom has to step in to solve it.)

348
00:15:44,238 --> 00:15:46,072
The cherry blossoms are pretty, right?

349
00:15:47,238 --> 00:15:48,105
Mom.
Look at that bus over there.

350
00:15:49,638 --> 00:15:51,472
Yu Jun, should we go for a walk?

351
00:15:51,472 --> 00:15:52,438
Let's go have some fun.
Let's go down the stairs.

352
00:15:54,005 --> 00:15:55,705
Yu Jun, it's raining.

353
00:15:56,172 --> 00:15:57,138
Are you happy?

354
00:15:57,438 --> 00:16:00,005
As long as you're happy, I'm happy too.

355
00:16:02,472 --> 00:16:04,172
- In 1, 2.
- In 1, 2.

356
00:16:04,172 --> 00:16:06,772
(Doing Yu Jun's favorite activity,
while tightly holding both hands)

357
00:16:08,905 --> 00:16:11,005
Yu Jun, you walk so well.

358
00:16:11,005 --> 00:16:12,372
- How brave.
- Really.

359
00:16:12,805 --> 00:16:13,972
Look at me.

360
00:16:14,972 --> 00:16:16,172
- You're going out again?
- Again?

361
00:16:16,638 --> 00:16:17,638
Do you want to go down the stairs again?

362
00:16:18,705 --> 00:16:20,138
Let's walk over there.

363
00:16:21,738 --> 00:16:23,638
Now let's go home. Good job.

364
00:16:23,972 --> 00:16:26,038
All right. Let's go back in.

365
00:16:26,038 --> 00:16:28,605
(At 5:10 p.m.,
going back home after a brief walk)

366
00:16:30,638 --> 00:16:31,672
That's really cool.

367
00:16:31,672 --> 00:16:33,105
You really flexed today, right?

368
00:16:33,105 --> 00:16:34,705
(Surprised)

369
00:16:35,205 --> 00:16:36,838
- Who could it be?
- Oh, my.

370
00:16:36,838 --> 00:16:37,772
Hello.

371
00:16:38,138 --> 00:16:39,605
Your mommy is here.

372
00:16:39,605 --> 00:16:41,472
He's so happy to see his mom. Gosh.

373
00:16:42,672 --> 00:16:44,538
Yu Jun, you did so well...

374
00:16:44,538 --> 00:16:46,305
playing with us today.

375
00:16:47,005 --> 00:16:49,172
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

376
00:16:49,172 --> 00:16:50,172
Yu Jun, "I love you."

377
00:16:50,172 --> 00:16:51,638
"I love you."

378
00:16:52,572 --> 00:16:54,072
High-five!

379
00:16:54,072 --> 00:16:55,005
Yu Jun, high-five.

380
00:16:56,105 --> 00:16:57,138
Let's go home, Yu Jun.

381
00:16:57,138 --> 00:16:58,505
(We're officially off babysitting duty.)

382
00:16:58,505 --> 00:16:59,572
See you next week.

383
00:17:00,772 --> 00:17:02,072
What should I write?

384
00:17:02,072 --> 00:17:06,105
Today felt really meaningful to me...

385
00:17:06,105 --> 00:17:08,838
because Yu Jun opened up to me a lot more.

386
00:17:08,838 --> 00:17:13,605
"Today, just the two of us babysat him,"

387
00:17:13,605 --> 00:17:16,138
"but he got so much more affectionate..."

388
00:17:16,138 --> 00:17:17,905
That's so right.

389
00:17:17,905 --> 00:17:18,938
And he kept wanting to be held.

390
00:17:18,938 --> 00:17:20,805
Last time, he didn't try to come to me.

391
00:17:20,805 --> 00:17:22,305
He ate really well too.

392
00:17:22,305 --> 00:17:25,372
"He cleaned his plate completely."

393
00:17:25,372 --> 00:17:28,772
"He was really popular
at the kids' cafe too."

394
00:17:28,772 --> 00:17:32,705
"He took a good nap..."

395
00:17:32,705 --> 00:17:36,138
"and also enjoyed his snacks afterward."

396
00:17:36,338 --> 00:17:43,438
"I think this gave us more confidence
that we can take better care of him..."

397
00:17:43,438 --> 00:17:45,072
"going forward..."

398
00:17:45,072 --> 00:17:46,438
- Right?
- Of course.

399
00:17:46,438 --> 00:17:48,005
- I feel more confident now.
- Me too.

400
00:17:48,005 --> 00:17:52,772
"Please trust us with Yu Jun."

401
00:17:53,238 --> 00:17:54,505
"Thank you."

402
00:18:02,538 --> 00:18:05,405
(At 8:30 a.m., babysitting at work?)

403
00:18:05,405 --> 00:18:07,905
(TOMORROW X TOGETHER Green Room)

404
00:18:08,138 --> 00:18:10,438
(TOMORROW X TOGETHER is
on "Show! Music Core")

405
00:18:10,772 --> 00:18:14,638
(Getting all dolled up
for the pre-recording)

406
00:18:14,772 --> 00:18:17,605
(The idol aspect we haven't seen
for a while)

407
00:18:17,905 --> 00:18:20,738
(And the baby items here and there)

408
00:18:20,738 --> 00:18:22,305
(Their green room has become a daycare.)

409
00:18:22,305 --> 00:18:24,872
(The little baby,
the owner of all the items)

410
00:18:26,005 --> 00:18:29,705
(YEONJUN, an idol,
has now become a daddy.)

411
00:18:29,972 --> 00:18:32,872
(Babysitting while waiting
for his turn for makeup)

412
00:18:35,072 --> 00:18:37,338
(Now, YEONJUN can hold him
much more naturally.)

413
00:18:37,338 --> 00:18:38,238
Let's go over there.

414
00:18:38,605 --> 00:18:40,472
Say hi.

415
00:18:40,472 --> 00:18:42,505
(Yu Jun is here!)

416
00:18:43,638 --> 00:18:44,605
Hi.
High-five.

417
00:18:45,638 --> 00:18:47,272
(Plump cheeks)

418
00:18:47,572 --> 00:18:50,238
(Yu Jun's fanboy is melting
from how cute he is.)

419
00:18:50,238 --> 00:18:53,005
(Cuddling Yu Jun, who's become closer
after the last time)

420
00:18:53,172 --> 00:18:54,772
Yu Jun, there's BEOMGYU.

421
00:18:55,672 --> 00:18:56,638
BEOMGYU!

422
00:18:56,972 --> 00:18:58,172
Say hi to him.

423
00:18:59,205 --> 00:19:00,405
You remember BEOMGYU?

424
00:19:00,405 --> 00:19:02,005
Good boy.

425
00:19:03,205 --> 00:19:05,005
(Fully charged with Yu Jun's energy
after a handshake)

426
00:19:05,005 --> 00:19:06,205
You even know how to shake hands?

427
00:19:06,572 --> 00:19:07,805
Yu Jun.

428
00:19:07,805 --> 00:19:09,205
(I want this.)

429
00:19:09,205 --> 00:19:10,038
You want this?

430
00:19:11,038 --> 00:19:14,005
(Overflowing with love
even when giving him snacks)

431
00:19:14,738 --> 00:19:15,772
How adorable.

432
00:19:17,305 --> 00:19:18,238
Is it good?
(It's yummy.)

433
00:19:21,872 --> 00:19:23,772
You're eating well by yourself.

434
00:19:25,172 --> 00:19:26,738
Wait. Look at your hand.

435
00:19:26,738 --> 00:19:27,805
Look how dirty it got.

436
00:19:28,838 --> 00:19:30,338
Yu Jun, what happened to your hand?

437
00:19:30,338 --> 00:19:31,205
(Mindless)

438
00:19:31,805 --> 00:19:33,172
(On-the-spot cleaning service again)

439
00:19:33,172 --> 00:19:34,938
Yu Jun, what happened to your hand?

440
00:19:35,372 --> 00:19:36,205
Why is it so dirty?

441
00:19:36,938 --> 00:19:39,738
(Are you wiping it again?)

442
00:19:40,305 --> 00:19:41,438
You don't like it? Okay.

443
00:19:43,772 --> 00:19:47,105
(I'm in charge
of Yu Jun's spotless appearance.)

444
00:19:48,238 --> 00:19:49,505
(A final pat)

445
00:19:51,138 --> 00:19:55,005
(YEONJUN is getting his makeup done
to go on stage.)

446
00:19:55,372 --> 00:19:57,772
(Meanwhile, Yu Jun is playing on his own.)

447
00:19:58,238 --> 00:20:00,338
(What's this?)

448
00:20:01,220 --> 00:20:02,120
(Smash!)

449
00:20:02,388 --> 00:20:05,123
(The tower crumbles down
with a single hit.)

450
00:20:06,325 --> 00:20:07,425
(Building)

451
00:20:07,893 --> 00:20:10,495
(Stacking food containers is fun.)

452
00:20:10,996 --> 00:20:13,498
(Babies always end up playing
with the most unexpected things.)

453
00:20:15,033 --> 00:20:18,068
(With his tiny little hands,
he successfully rebuilds the tower.)

454
00:20:18,404 --> 00:20:21,906
(Did you see that?)

455
00:20:22,174 --> 00:20:24,609
(He looks for more containers
for his tower.)

456
00:20:24,843 --> 00:20:26,744
(Shaking)

457
00:20:28,313 --> 00:20:30,781
(The tower master is picky
about his materials.)

458
00:20:31,183 --> 00:20:33,885
(This time, he checks whether a container
as big as himself will fit.)

459
00:20:34,052 --> 00:20:35,986
(It's too heavy.)

460
00:20:36,989 --> 00:20:38,323
(Putting it down)

461
00:20:38,624 --> 00:20:42,994
(Yu Jun carefully checks
the stability of his tower again.)

462
00:20:43,328 --> 00:20:46,597
(The chubby-cheeked builder is satisfied.)

463
00:20:47,032 --> 00:20:49,800
(Here comes the baby looking
for his next toy.)

464
00:20:49,801 --> 00:20:50,835
He's here.

465
00:20:51,470 --> 00:20:52,837
Hey, Yu Jun.

466
00:20:53,405 --> 00:20:55,206
(Looking away)

467
00:20:55,207 --> 00:20:56,340
Okay.

468
00:20:56,575 --> 00:20:58,309
It's okay. That happens.

469
00:20:58,777 --> 00:21:01,112
(The 15-month-old is playing hard to get.)

470
00:21:01,113 --> 00:21:03,280
Pay attention to me.

471
00:21:03,281 --> 00:21:05,082
Hey, baby Yu Jun.

472
00:21:05,083 --> 00:21:07,318
Baby? What's up?

473
00:21:07,486 --> 00:21:09,187
Hey, baby Yu Jun.

474
00:21:09,421 --> 00:21:10,454
Yu Jun.

475
00:21:10,455 --> 00:21:11,722
(Floundering)

476
00:21:11,957 --> 00:21:14,058
(Should I give him my hand?)

477
00:21:15,561 --> 00:21:17,129
(Not now.)

478
00:21:17,130 --> 00:21:18,162
Yu Jun.

479
00:21:18,163 --> 00:21:19,731
(His fingertips stretch
with lingering feelings.)

480
00:21:19,900 --> 00:21:21,933
(HUENINGKAI comes over
after finishing his makeup.)

481
00:21:21,934 --> 00:21:23,368
What's this?

482
00:21:24,002 --> 00:21:26,270
(Very quiet)

483
00:21:26,271 --> 00:21:28,205
Has he always been this quiet?

484
00:21:29,007 --> 00:21:29,907
He's never really been talkative.

485
00:21:29,908 --> 00:21:31,309
(I can't talk.)

486
00:21:31,877 --> 00:21:33,878
Does he usually say a word or two?

487
00:21:33,879 --> 00:21:35,313
(Yu Jun is giving everyone
the cold shoulder today.)

488
00:21:35,981 --> 00:21:39,583
Hey, do you want some food? Nom-nom?

489
00:21:41,453 --> 00:21:42,453
Is it there?

490
00:21:42,454 --> 00:21:43,988
(Nom-nom?)

491
00:21:43,989 --> 00:21:45,122
Let me see.

492
00:21:45,324 --> 00:21:46,690
Yu Jun really loves food.

493
00:21:46,691 --> 00:21:48,993
He always reacts when we say "food."

494
00:21:49,194 --> 00:21:50,261
Nom-nom.

495
00:21:50,262 --> 00:21:52,163
(It's time for Yu Jun to eat!)

496
00:21:52,631 --> 00:21:54,899
(A baby's meal appears
backstage at a music show.)

497
00:21:55,367 --> 00:21:58,035
(The food catches his eye!)

498
00:21:59,071 --> 00:22:01,773
(Give it to me now!)

499
00:22:02,474 --> 00:22:04,108
That's it!

500
00:22:04,510 --> 00:22:07,245
(The way he chews is so satisfying.)

501
00:22:08,347 --> 00:22:09,781
What a good boy.

502
00:22:10,250 --> 00:22:13,238
(I'm not letting go!)

503
00:22:13,652 --> 00:22:14,685
Open up.

504
00:22:15,020 --> 00:22:16,954
(Yum!)

505
00:22:16,955 --> 00:22:19,156
(Here comes the food airplane!)

506
00:22:19,157 --> 00:22:20,358
Do you want a fork too?

507
00:22:20,826 --> 00:22:21,826
He's really eating up.

508
00:22:23,028 --> 00:22:25,763
- That's it.
- How cute.

509
00:22:25,764 --> 00:22:27,358
(A rare sight
in a "Show! Music Core" waiting room)

510
00:22:27,359 --> 00:22:29,734
Yu Jun likes doing everything himself.

511
00:22:30,302 --> 00:22:32,603
(He scoops up the food and feeds himself.)

512
00:22:32,604 --> 00:22:33,771
Is it good?

513
00:22:34,072 --> 00:22:35,172
Good job.

514
00:22:35,374 --> 00:22:38,910
(This waiting room restaurant is amazing.)

515
00:22:39,545 --> 00:22:41,212
You're eating so well by yourself now.

516
00:22:41,213 --> 00:22:42,747
- So yummy!
- Nice.

517
00:22:43,148 --> 00:22:45,049
What a good boy!

518
00:22:45,050 --> 00:22:47,718
He's such a good eater.
He can feed himself now.

519
00:22:48,787 --> 00:22:50,054
That's it.

520
00:22:50,055 --> 00:22:52,523
(He finishes his meal in no time.)

521
00:22:54,092 --> 00:22:56,627
- Do you have the baby wipes?
- Yes.

522
00:22:56,628 --> 00:22:58,896
(The foodie gets another refill.)

523
00:23:00,032 --> 00:23:01,332
He smiles after every bite.

524
00:23:02,535 --> 00:23:04,302
- See?
- How delicious!

525
00:23:04,603 --> 00:23:06,837
What a lovely smile.

526
00:23:07,272 --> 00:23:09,139
- That's it!
- It's so good!

527
00:23:09,140 --> 00:23:12,643
(Yu Jun loves their reactions.)

528
00:23:12,644 --> 00:23:14,044
Yummy!

529
00:23:14,045 --> 00:23:15,179
Well done.

530
00:23:15,180 --> 00:23:16,547
(What a good boy!)

531
00:23:16,949 --> 00:23:18,016
Done.

532
00:23:18,017 --> 00:23:19,450
(His satisfying breakfast is over.)

533
00:23:19,952 --> 00:23:22,587
(Wiping his face after eating is a must.)

534
00:23:22,588 --> 00:23:24,055
Wipe his face a little.

535
00:23:24,256 --> 00:23:25,356
Drink up.

536
00:23:26,124 --> 00:23:29,827
(You need a cup of water after a meal.)

537
00:23:30,162 --> 00:23:31,529
(He changes into a new bib.)

538
00:23:31,530 --> 00:23:33,865
- I got one.
- There.

539
00:23:33,866 --> 00:23:35,566
You're enjoying your water!

540
00:23:35,902 --> 00:23:37,502
(The parenting continues
in the waiting room.)

541
00:23:37,503 --> 00:23:38,569
Was it good?

542
00:23:39,471 --> 00:23:40,505
Nice job.

543
00:23:40,506 --> 00:23:42,573
- That was a good meal.
- Right.

544
00:23:42,574 --> 00:23:44,708
- I give it five stars.
- He says he liked it.

545
00:23:44,709 --> 00:23:46,744
(Perfect breakfast)

546
00:23:47,112 --> 00:23:48,946
(Singing)

547
00:23:49,381 --> 00:23:51,482
(What is he doing?)

548
00:23:51,984 --> 00:23:53,518
I need to warm up my vocals.

549
00:23:53,986 --> 00:23:55,252
(Singing)

550
00:23:56,255 --> 00:23:57,488
- He copied me.
- I know.

551
00:23:57,489 --> 00:23:59,924
(Show me your cute singing again.)

552
00:24:00,626 --> 00:24:02,493
(Smiling)

553
00:24:02,494 --> 00:24:03,861
Good job.

554
00:24:04,062 --> 00:24:05,323
(Singing)

555
00:24:06,131 --> 00:24:08,165
(Burping)

556
00:24:08,166 --> 00:24:09,133
Did you burp?

557
00:24:10,068 --> 00:24:12,302
Where do you want to go?
Do you want to go outside? Let's go.

558
00:24:13,872 --> 00:24:15,406
There are lots
of strangers out here, right?

559
00:24:15,407 --> 00:24:16,507
Are you sure you can handle it?

560
00:24:18,010 --> 00:24:20,144
(He expands his territory
in front of the elevators.)

561
00:24:20,545 --> 00:24:23,080
(Confidently walking)

562
00:24:24,816 --> 00:24:27,217
Yu Jun, that's the women's restroom.
You can't go in there.

563
00:24:28,053 --> 00:24:30,955
Yu Jun. No, you can't go in there.

564
00:24:31,723 --> 00:24:32,756
Hold on.

565
00:24:32,757 --> 00:24:34,625
(He can't resist the instinct
to explore further.)

566
00:24:34,860 --> 00:24:36,227
(Gets caught in front
of the women's restroom)

567
00:24:36,228 --> 00:24:38,196
You're not allowed to go
into the women's restroom.

568
00:24:39,264 --> 00:24:40,898
(Where am I going now?)

569
00:24:42,861 --> 00:24:44,168
Why were you arrested?

570
00:24:44,169 --> 00:24:45,936
He tried to go into the women's restroom.

571
00:24:46,405 --> 00:24:47,605
I couldn't help you there.

572
00:24:47,606 --> 00:24:49,006
Even if you did, I couldn't.

573
00:24:49,741 --> 00:24:50,941
You'd have to get yourself out
of that one.

574
00:24:51,810 --> 00:24:52,811
Where are we going now?

575
00:24:52,812 --> 00:24:53,878
(Heads out with his favorite toy.)

576
00:24:55,547 --> 00:24:57,214
The hallways aren't crowded right now.

577
00:24:57,215 --> 00:24:59,149
But they will be soon.
What are you going to do then?

578
00:24:59,150 --> 00:25:00,251
Tell me.

579
00:25:00,419 --> 00:25:01,452
Hold on.

580
00:25:01,453 --> 00:25:03,855
Sorry.

581
00:25:04,423 --> 00:25:05,857
Sorry.

582
00:25:06,391 --> 00:25:07,524
Excuse us.

583
00:25:08,060 --> 00:25:10,028
Excuse us. Coming through.

584
00:25:11,830 --> 00:25:16,767
(Thanks to Manager HUENINGKAI,
the ride is going smoothly.)

585
00:25:17,536 --> 00:25:19,637
Look at you.
You're bumping into everything.

586
00:25:19,638 --> 00:25:21,005
(He protects his artist at all costs.)

587
00:25:22,441 --> 00:25:23,441
(They safely return to the waiting room.)

588
00:25:23,442 --> 00:25:25,076
We're back!

589
00:25:25,077 --> 00:25:26,812
(The manager is relieved
to wrap things up early.)

590
00:25:26,813 --> 00:25:28,679
The tour is over.

591
00:25:29,715 --> 00:25:31,049
Okay. You want to go out again.

592
00:25:31,050 --> 00:25:33,284
We're heading out again. He wants to go.

593
00:25:35,487 --> 00:25:36,921
(We're back again.)

594
00:25:36,922 --> 00:25:38,189
The tour is over.

595
00:25:40,325 --> 00:25:42,326
You're such a free spirit.

596
00:25:42,327 --> 00:25:43,494
Don't know what you'll do next.

597
00:25:43,495 --> 00:25:44,828
(Yu Jun changes his mind every second.)

598
00:25:44,829 --> 00:25:46,530
You want to go in? Okay.

599
00:25:46,531 --> 00:25:48,699
(I'm going in again.)

600
00:25:49,468 --> 00:25:52,804
(No, I'm not.)

601
00:25:53,105 --> 00:25:56,040
That's it. Good job.
You keep discovering new paths.

602
00:25:57,342 --> 00:26:01,445
(Artist Yu Jun's Hallway Cart Tour
continues!)

603
00:26:01,446 --> 00:26:05,015
(Confident)

604
00:26:05,717 --> 00:26:06,917
Excuse us.

605
00:26:08,253 --> 00:26:09,386
That's it.

606
00:26:10,088 --> 00:26:12,623
- Sorry.
- Don't worry.

607
00:26:12,891 --> 00:26:14,358
That's it.

608
00:26:15,093 --> 00:26:17,995
Choo-choo train

609
00:26:18,563 --> 00:26:21,865
(The manager's back is permanently bent
from the artist's busy schedule.)

610
00:26:22,934 --> 00:26:23,934
Let's go.

611
00:26:24,503 --> 00:26:25,570
(This deserves a raise, right?)

612
00:26:25,571 --> 00:26:27,839
Look who's back!

613
00:26:29,274 --> 00:26:30,541
I need to get changed now.

614
00:26:31,243 --> 00:26:32,376
The tour is over.

615
00:26:32,377 --> 00:26:34,319
We met staff members
from the other waiting rooms too.

616
00:26:34,320 --> 00:26:36,013
(He recharges with rice crackers
after a successful tour.)

617
00:26:36,982 --> 00:26:39,951
(Twenty minutes before going on stage)

618
00:26:40,285 --> 00:26:42,353
(The waiting room becomes even busier.)

619
00:26:42,721 --> 00:26:46,891
(The uncles are getting ready
for the performance.)

620
00:26:47,058 --> 00:26:49,293
(Vocal warm-up)

621
00:26:49,928 --> 00:26:52,596
(He's warming up too.)

622
00:26:52,797 --> 00:26:55,499
(Yu Jun returns
after another round of touring.)

623
00:26:55,500 --> 00:26:57,467
That's it. Okay, let's get inside.

624
00:26:57,769 --> 00:26:59,737
Why do you look sad?

625
00:26:59,738 --> 00:27:00,904
For real?

626
00:27:01,540 --> 00:27:02,773
Are you sure?

627
00:27:02,974 --> 00:27:05,108
(Flustered)

628
00:27:05,510 --> 00:27:08,045
(Crying)

629
00:27:08,046 --> 00:27:10,180
(He suddenly bursts into tears.)

630
00:27:10,549 --> 00:27:12,517
That's it.

631
00:27:12,884 --> 00:27:14,151
(Is he upset because they're all busy?)

632
00:27:14,152 --> 00:27:15,853
Really? Is that so?

633
00:27:16,588 --> 00:27:17,922
I see.

634
00:27:17,923 --> 00:27:19,924
Yu Jun.

635
00:27:19,925 --> 00:27:21,158
(Worried)

636
00:27:21,159 --> 00:27:22,993
- Yu Jun.
- He's getting sweaty.

637
00:27:22,994 --> 00:27:27,131
(His crying only gets more intense.)

638
00:27:27,833 --> 00:27:28,966
(Worried)

639
00:27:28,967 --> 00:27:30,735
Yu Jun.

640
00:27:30,869 --> 00:27:33,604
(Ten minutes before going on stage)

641
00:27:33,972 --> 00:27:37,608
(He has to stop crying now.)

642
00:27:37,709 --> 00:27:39,910
(His pacifier is urgently brought in.)

643
00:27:39,911 --> 00:27:41,845
Oh, yes! Pacifier!

644
00:27:41,846 --> 00:27:43,380
Are you calm now, Yu Jun?

645
00:27:43,381 --> 00:27:44,548
(Is the pacifier working?)

646
00:27:44,549 --> 00:27:47,885
(No, it's not!)

647
00:27:48,086 --> 00:27:51,855
(Yu Jun has
absolutely no intention of stopping.)

648
00:27:52,090 --> 00:27:53,891
(Wailing)

649
00:27:56,394 --> 00:27:57,594
(They bring over Yu Jun's favorite milk.)

650
00:27:57,595 --> 00:27:59,463
(No!)

651
00:27:59,764 --> 00:28:02,599
(He even refuses his favorite milk.)

652
00:28:03,068 --> 00:28:04,735
(Five minutes before the performance...)

653
00:28:04,736 --> 00:28:08,373
(and Yu Jun still won't stop crying!)
